---
// Scroll-driven demonstration: the article table collapses, then a Kafka
// sentence is "processed" rule by rule like a form at an office, ending
// with the official stamp. Progress is driven by an IntersectionObserver
// setting data-step on the section; all visuals react via CSS classes.
---

<section class="scrolly" id="demo" data-step="0">
  <header class="scrolly-lead">
    <p class="kicker">Amtliche Vorführung</p>
    <h2>German, simplified.</h2>
    <p class="sub">A guided demonstration in seven steps. Scroll to proceed.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="scrolly-body">
    <div class="scrolly-stage">
      <!-- Stage A: the declension table -->
      <div class="stage-card stage-table">
        <div class="card-head">
          <span>Anlage 1</span>
          <span>Bestimmter Artikel, Standarddeutsch</span>
        </div>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th></th><th>Mask.</th><th>Fem.</th><th>Neut.</th><th>Plural</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th>Nominativ</th>
              <td><del>der</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">die</td>
              <td><del>das</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">die</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Akkusativ</th>
              <td><del>den</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">die</td>
              <td><del>das</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">die</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Dativ</th>
              <td><del>dem</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td><del>der</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td><del>dem</del><ins>die</ins></td>
              <td><del>den</del><ins>die</ins></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="gen">
              <th>Genitiv</th>
              <td><del>des</del><ins>der</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">der</td>
              <td><del>des</del><ins>der</ins></td>
              <td class="stays">der</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p class="table-verdict">Sechzehn Felder. Zwei Formen.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stage B: the specimen document -->
      <div class="stage-card stage-doc">
        <div class="card-head">
          <span>Formblatt AL-2</span>
          <span>Antrag auf Vereinfachung</span>
        </div>
        <p class="doc-source">
          Eingang: F. Kafka, <em>Die Verwandlung</em> (1915), Satz 1
        </p>
        <p class="doc-sentence">
          Als Gregor Samsa
          <span class="tok" data-at="3"><del>eines Morgens</del><ins>ein Morgen</ins></span>
          aus
          <span class="tok" data-at="5"><del>unruhigen</del><ins>unruhige</ins></span>
          <span class="tok" data-at="4"><del>Träumen</del><ins>Träume</ins></span>
          erwachte, fand er sich in
          <span class="tok" data-at="6"><del>seinem</del><ins>sein</ins></span>
          Bett zu
          <span class="tok" data-at="3"><del>einem</del><ins>ein</ins></span>
          <span class="tok" data-at="5"><del>ungeheueren</del><ins>ungeheure</ins></span>
          Ungeziefer verwandelt.
        </p>
        <div class="doc-chips" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="chip" data-at="3">§2a</span>
          <span class="chip" data-at="4">§3a</span>
          <span class="chip" data-at="5">§4a</span>
          <span class="chip" data-at="6">§7c</span>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-clean" data-at="7">
          <p class="clean-label">Reinschrift</p>
          <p class="clean-sentence">
            Als Gregor Samsa ein Morgen aus unruhige Träume erwachte, fand er
            sich in sein Bett zu ein ungeheure Ungeziefer verwandelt.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="stamp" data-at="7" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="stamp-emblem"></span>
          <span class="stamp-line1">Amtlich vereinfacht</span>
          <span class="stamp-line2">Geprüft · §1–§10</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="scrolly-steps">
      <div class="step" data-step="0">
        <p class="step-kicker">Schritt 1 · Befund</p>
        <p>
          Standard German declines its definite article across three genders,
          four cases and two numbers. Sixteen slots, six forms — and every
          noun's gender must be memorized before any of them can be used.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="1">
        <p class="step-kicker">Schritt 2 · §1a, §1b</p>
        <p>
          Alman files fifteen of them away. Every non-genitive context
          receives <strong>die</strong>. The genitive receives
          <strong>der</strong>. Nothing else survives the procedure.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="2">
        <p class="step-kicker">Schritt 3 · Eingang</p>
        <p>
          The procedure extends beyond articles. A specimen is submitted for
          processing: the opening sentence of Kafka's
          <em>Die Verwandlung</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="3">
        <p class="step-kicker">Schritt 4 · §2a</p>
        <p>
          The indefinite article adopts its invariant base form
          <strong>ein</strong>. Case endings are discarded:
          <em>eines Morgens</em> and <em>einem</em> are corrected.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="4">
        <p class="step-kicker">Schritt 5 · §3a</p>
        <p>
          Case endings on nouns are eliminated. The dative plural
          <em>Träumen</em> loses its <em>-n</em> and reverts to the plain
          plural <em>Träume</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="5">
        <p class="step-kicker">Schritt 6 · §4a</p>
        <p>
          Adjective endings regularize to an invariant <strong>-e</strong>:
          <em>unruhigen</em> becomes <em>unruhige</em>,
          <em>ungeheueren</em> becomes <em>ungeheure</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="6">
        <p class="step-kicker">Schritt 7 · §7c</p>
        <p>
          Possessive determiners keep their bare base form in all non-genitive
          contexts: <em>seinem Bett</em> is corrected to
          <em>sein Bett</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="step" data-step="7">
        <p class="step-kicker">Bescheid</p>
        <p>
          Processing complete. The sentence remains fully intelligible to any
          German speaker — with none of the declension machinery. The full
          procedure is codified below in
          <a href="#definite-articles">§1–§10</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  const section = document.getElementById("demo")!;
  const steps = section.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>(".step");

  function apply(step: number) {
    section.dataset.step = String(step);
    section
      .querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>("[data-at]")
      .forEach((el) => {
        el.classList.toggle("done", step >= Number(el.dataset.at));
      });
  }

  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      for (const entry of entries) {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          apply(Number((entry.target as HTMLElement).dataset.step));
        }
      }
    },
    { rootMargin: "-40% 0px -50% 0px" },
  );
  steps.forEach((el) => observer.observe(el));
</script>

<style>
  /* Full-bleed breakout from the 50rem main column */
  .scrolly {
    width: 100vw;
    margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem 4rem;
  }

  .scrolly-lead {
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    margin: 0 auto 1rem;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .kicker,
  .step-kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--grey-1);
  }

  .scrolly-lead h2 {
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.3rem;
    font-size: 2.3rem;
  }

  .scrolly-lead .sub {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--grey-1);
  }

  .scrolly-body {
    max-width: 66rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(15rem, 20rem) 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  /* ---------- Stage ---------- */

  .scrolly-stage {
    order: 2;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    height: 100vh;
    height: 100dvh;
    display: grid;
    align-items: center;
    justify-items: center;
  }

  .stage-card {
    background: #ffffff;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem 1.75rem;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 34rem;
    grid-area: 1 / 1;
    position: relative;
    transition: opacity 0.45s ease, visibility 0.45s;
  }

  .card-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--grey-1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
    padding-bottom: 0.55rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
  }

  /* Table stage */
  .stage-table table {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .stage-table th {
    border: none;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.6rem;
  }

  .stage-table tbody th {
    text-align: left;
    color: var(--grey-1);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .stage-table td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--grey-2);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.6rem;
    font-family: var(--font-din);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    width: 21%;
  }

  .stage-table td del {
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease;
  }

  .stage-table td ins {
    display: none;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--form-blue);
  }

  .stage-table td.stays {
    transition: color 0.5s ease;
  }

  /* collapsed state (step >= 1) */
  [data-step]:not([data-step="0"]) .stage-table td del {
    display: none;
  }

  [data-step]:not([data-step="0"]) .stage-table td ins {
    display: inline;
  }

  [data-step]:not([data-step="0"]) .stage-table td.stays {
    color: var(--form-blue);
  }

  .table-verdict {
    margin: 1.2rem 0 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--grey-1);
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease 0.3s;
  }

  [data-step]:not([data-step="0"]) .table-verdict {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  /* Stage swap: table visible for steps 0-1, doc from step 2 on */
  .stage-doc {
    opacity: 0;
    visibility: hidden;
  }

  [data-step="2"] .stage-doc,
  [data-step="3"] .stage-doc,
  [data-step="4"] .stage-doc,
  [data-step="5"] .stage-doc,
  [data-step="6"] .stage-doc,
  [data-step="7"] .stage-doc {
    opacity: 1;
    visibility: visible;
  }

  [data-step="2"] .stage-table,
  [data-step="3"] .stage-table,
  [data-step="4"] .stage-table,
  [data-step="5"] .stage-table,
  [data-step="6"] .stage-table,
  [data-step="7"] .stage-table {
    opacity: 0;
    visibility: hidden;
  }

  /* Document stage */
  .doc-source {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--grey-1);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .doc-sentence {
    font-size: 1.12rem;
    line-height: 2;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tok del {
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
  }

  .tok ins {
    display: none;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--form-blue);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .tok.done del {
    text-decoration: line-through;
    text-decoration-color: var(--fail-red);
    text-decoration-thickness: 1.5px;
    opacity: 0.45;
    margin-right: 0.3em;
  }

  .tok.done ins {
    display: inline;
  }

  .doc-chips {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    min-height: 1.6rem;
  }

  .chip {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--form-blue);
    color: var(--form-blue);
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.45rem;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(4px);
    transition: opacity 0.35s ease, transform 0.35s ease;
  }

  .chip.done {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: none;
  }

  .doc-clean {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--grey-2);
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    padding-right: 9.5rem;
    min-height: 5.5rem;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease 0.15s;
  }

  .doc-clean.done {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .clean-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--grey-1);
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
  }

  .clean-sentence {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--form-blue);
  }

  /* Stamp */
  .stamp {
    position: absolute;
    right: 1.4rem;
    bottom: 1.1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.15rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem 0.7rem;
    border: 2.5px solid var(--form-blue);
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1.5px #ffffff, inset 0 0 0 2.5px var(--form-blue);
    color: var(--form-blue);
    transform: rotate(-8deg) scale(1.6);
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.25s ease, transform 0.25s cubic-bezier(0.2, 1.4, 0.4, 1);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .stamp.done {
    opacity: 0.92;
    transform: rotate(-8deg) scale(1);
  }

  .stamp-emblem {
    display: block;
    width: 2.1rem;
    height: 1.6rem;
    background: var(--form-blue);
    -webkit-mask: url("/assets/brand/alman_institut_logo.svg") no-repeat center / contain;
    mask: url("/assets/brand/alman_institut_logo.svg") no-repeat center / contain;
  }

  .stamp-line1 {
    font-family: var(--font-din);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .stamp-line2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  /* ---------- Steps ---------- */

  .scrolly-steps {
    order: 1;
  }

  .step {
    min-height: 88vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  .step p:not(.step-kicker) {
    background: var(--paper);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .step:first-child {
    min-height: 60vh;
  }

  .step:last-child {
    min-height: 95vh;
  }

  /* ---------- Mobile ---------- */

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .scrolly-body {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0;
    }

    .scrolly-stage {
      order: 1;
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      height: auto;
      padding: 0.6rem 0;
      background: var(--paper);
      z-index: 3;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .stage-card {
      padding: 0.85rem 1rem 1rem;
    }

    .card-head {
      font-size: 0.58rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      padding-bottom: 0.45rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
    }

    .card-head span {
      white-space: nowrap;
    }

    .stage-table td {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }

    .doc-source {
      font-size: 0.64rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
    }

    .doc-sentence {
      font-size: 0.94rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
    }

    .doc-chips {
      margin-top: 0.8rem;
      min-height: 1.4rem;
    }

    .doc-clean {
      margin-top: 0.8rem;
      padding-top: 0.7rem;
      padding-right: 0;
      min-height: 0;
    }

    .clean-sentence {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .scrolly-steps {
      order: 2;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
    }

    .step {
      min-height: 60vh;
      justify-content: flex-end;
      padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
      z-index: 1;
    }

    .step p:not(.step-kicker) {
      border: 1px solid var(--grey-2);
      border-radius: 2px;
      padding: 0.8rem 1rem;
    }

    /* Stamped across the document, like a real rubber stamp */
    .stamp {
      right: auto;
      left: 50%;
      bottom: 2.6rem;
      transform: translateX(-50%) rotate(-8deg) scale(1.6);
    }

    .stamp.done {
      transform: translateX(-50%) rotate(-8deg) scale(0.9);
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .stage-card,
    .tok del,
    .chip,
    .doc-clean,
    .stamp,
    .table-verdict {
      transition: none;
    }
  }
</style>
